  "prompt": "What is trauma?",
  "response": "Trauma is a psychological and emotional response to a deeply distressing or disturbing event or experience that overwhelms an individual's ability to cope. It can be caused by:\n\n1. Acute events:\n- Physical or sexual assault\n- Accidents\n- Natural disasters\n- Witnessing violence\n- Combat experiences\n\n2. Prolonged experiences:\n- Childhood abuse\n- Domestic violence\n- Chronic neglect\n- Long-term medical conditions\n- Ongoing discrimination or oppression\n\nTrauma can result in various psychological and physiological responses, including:\n\nPsychological effects:\n- Anxiety\n- Depression\n- Post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD)\n- Emotional numbness\n- Hypervigilance\n- Intrusive memories or flashbacks\n- Difficulty trusting others\n\nPhysiological effects:\n- Disrupted sleep patterns\n- Changes in brain chemistry\n- Increased stress hormone production\n- Heightened fight-or-flight response\n- Potential physical health issues\n\nTreatment typically involves:\n- Therapy (cognitive-behavioral, EMDR)\n- Counseling\n- Medication\n- Support groups\n- Holistic healing approaches\n\nTrauma is a complex experience that affects individuals differently and can have long-lasting impacts on mental and physical health.",
